Cytopathology is a subspecialty of pathology. A cytopathologist is proficient in interpreting diseases based on specimens containing cells. The cells may be collected by variety of way ranging from simple body fluids (such as urine, sputum, serous effusions) to specimens obtained with special procedures such as fine needle aspiration biopsy. The interpretation involves correlation of cytomorphological features in light of various clinical details and other ancillary tests such as immunoreactivity profile, cytogenetics, microbiology cultures, ultrastrucutural details, serological findings etc.